<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06243247 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06243247 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  WORLD; TRACK; CHAMPIONSHIP; TOKYO; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Dan O'Brien won the decathlon for the American team's eighth gold in the WorldTrack and Field Championships. His victory, combined with America's sweep inthe long jump, gave the United States an 8-7 lead in gold medals and 20-19lead in overall medals.;   O'Brien's total of 8,812 points was the thirdhighest ever for the decathlon and an American record. He broke the mark of8,634 set by Bruce Jenner in the 1976 Olympics in Montreal, the last time anAmerican won the event in a major international meet.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  AMERICAN O'BRIEN WINS DECATHLON  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  World Track and Field Championships  </MEMO><TEXT>     Daley Thompson of Britain set the world record of 8,847 in the 1984Olympics in Los Angeles.;   Michael Smith was second today with 8,549 points,a Canadian national record, and Christian Schenk of Germany third with 8,394.;  O'Brien needed to run the 1,500 meters, the last event of the competition,in 4 minutes, 32.14 seconds for a world record. But he could do no better than4:37.50 on a track soaked by a driving rain before the race.;   O'Brien wastops in the pole vault today, clearing the bar at 17 3/4, about 8 incheshigher than anyone else. He threw the javelin 199 feet, finishing third in hisgroup.;   In other events today, O'Brien was the best in the 110 hurdles witha time of 13.94, and he threw the discus 154-10.;   In the high jump onThursday, O'Brien did 6-3 1/4. Also on Thursday he did 25-11 in the long jump,ran the 100 in 10.41, the 400 in 43.56, did 53-3 1/2 in the shot put. Hisefforts in the 100 and 400 and the long jump were the best in thecompetition.;   In other events, Katrin Krabbe of Germany became the firstdouble gold-medal winner of the championships, dominating the women's 200meters in 22.09 seconds despite a strong head wind and driving rain.;   LizMcColgan captured Britain's first gold of the meet, leading the women's 10,000from start to finish. She finished in 31:14.31.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Tokyo  </CITY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910830  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  341  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday, August 30, 199100243247,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>